---
import '../styles/global.css';

const today = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Luqen — Accessibility compliance, with evidence</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Luqen scans, scores, and helps remediate WCAG accessibility issues across your sites. Evidence-grade reports, AI fix proposals, and Git-host integrations." />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
</head>
<body>
  <main>

    <section class="hero">
      <p class="hero__eyebrow">Luqen — WCAG accessibility</p>
      <h1>Know exactly where your website breaks accessibility law. Fix it before anyone else notices.</h1>
      <p class="hero__verdict">
        Self-scanned {today} · WCAG 2.2 AA · this page is the reference implementation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What we measure</p>
      <h2>Every rule, every page, every jurisdiction.</h2>
      <p>Luqen runs pa11y and axe-core against your site, scores every page against the WCAG 2.2 ruleset, and cross-references the findings against the legal regime that applies where your customers are. EU EAA, US ADA, UK PSBAR, and more, with named regulations attached to the rules that govern them.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What you ship</p>
      <h2>Evidence, not vibes.</h2>
      <p>Every claim links back to the rule, the selector, the code context, and an AI-proposed fix. Reports are board-readable and developer-actionable in the same document. The same numbers in the dashboard, in the PDF, and on the public report URL — never reconciled, never softened.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who we serve</p>
      <h2>Developers and compliance officers, on the same screen.</h2>
      <p>The dashboard is a docket, not a metric wall. The PDF is a court transcript, not a brochure. Switch between dense and plain modes per user. Hand the report to a regulator and to engineering, and both will trust what they read.</p>
    </section>

  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>Verified by Luqen · {today} · luqen.dev</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
